# Firebase Configuration
# 
# REQUIRED: You must set these environment variables for the application to work
# 
# To setup Firebase:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace the placeholder values below with your Firebase project configuration
# 3. Find these values in Firebase Console > Project Settings > General
#
# Example configuration (replace with your actual values):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIzaSyD...your-api-key
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project.firebasestorage.app
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=123456789
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:123456789:web:abc123
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-ABC123XYZ

# Admin email for dashboard access (optional)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com

# Optional: Base path for deployment (e.g., /GeoTracker for GitHub Pages)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_PATH=/GeoTracker

# ⚠️ IMPORTANT: Firebase Setup Required
# 
# If you're getting "auth/configuration-not-found" error:
# - This means Firebase Authentication is not enabled in your Firebase Console
# - See FIREBASE_SETUP.md for detailed setup instructions
# - You need to enable Email/Password and Anonymous authentication

